A proxy advisory firm, Egan-Jones Proxy Services, said today that it has put its support behind most of the nominees proposed by H.J. Heinz Co. for its board. Heinz is locked in a proxy battle with Trian Partners, an activist fund led by Nelson Peltz. While Egan-Jones said it would support most of the porposed slate, it said it would withold its support for two of the Heinz board nominees, Leonard Coleman Jr. and Edith Holiday, contending that they are already on too many corporate boards.

